comment: The placement of Mercurii as starting point and intermediate stop on the route does not make any sense. An alternative location could be at -6.98380, 33.86776 (km 23.268), which is also where the roman road ends. Distances in this route are almost perfectly accurate, so this location would make sense.
This location is correct

text_transcription: A Tingi litoribus navigatur usque ad Portus Divinos:
comment: I believe the text transcription is not an endpoint but a direction based on mode of transport. This is sort of an “internal route” to indicate that from Tingis to Portus Divinus the main mode of transportation is by boat. It is, therefore, an insertion in the route with navigational information, rather than an actual stop at this point in the route. The distance to Septem Fratres is, however, almost double the effective one.
